<p><h3><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Run-Time%20Code%20Generation">Run-Time Code Generation</a></h3>

<p><h3>Reflective Expert Systems</h3>
Jacques Pitrat and his team. <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://ai.eecs.umich.edu/cogarch3/CapabilLists/SelfReflect.html">Self Reflection in Cognitive Architectures</a>.

<p><h3>Reflective Concurrent Programming</h3>
<a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Jos%E9%20Meseguer">José Meseguer</a>; <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://www-formal.stanford.edu/clt/home.html">Carol Talcott</a>; <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/A.%20Yonezawa">A. Yonezawa</a>;

<p><h3><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Meta-Object%20Protocol">Meta-Object Protocol</a>s</h3>

<p>A classic book, <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/AMOP">AMOP</a>.

<p>A recent small project in <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Squeak">Squeak</a> by Henrik Gedenryd to develop a "Universal Composition" system for programs. It essentially involves a graph of meta-objects describing source-composition operations which can be eagerly or lazily (statically or dynamically) driven, resulting in <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/partial%20evaluation">partial evaluation</a> or forms of dynamic composition such as <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/AOP">AOP</a>. He provides <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://www.lucs.lu.se/People/Henrik.Gedenryd/Squeak/aspectblt.zip">a demonstration Squeak image</a> and <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://www.lucs.lu.se/People/Henrik.Gedenryd/Squeak/UC/UCpaper.pdf">a rough draft paper</a>.

<p><h3><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Aspect-Oriented%20Programming">Aspect-Oriented Programming</a></h3>

<p><a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/Gregor%20Kiczales">Gregor Kiczales</a>.

<p>See also <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/AspectJ">AspectJ</a> and <a class="internal" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20050208011029/http://cliki.tunes.org/AspectS">AspectS</a>.

